YOU CAN ALSO ENTER ONE OF THE FOLLOWING SLASH COMMANDS:

/dpy 1
Set dpy (dots per year) 1, that is, a dot represents a year.

/asof 2020/01/01_12:0:0
Set the time corresponding to the left edge of the bar to noon on January 1, 2020.

/sel -t word
Select tasks whose title contains 'word'.

/sel -s 2020/1/1_12:0:0< <2020/1/2
Select tasks whose start is in the afternoon of January 1, 2020.

/sel -d <23:59:59
Select tasks whose deadline is today's end.

/sel -w 30< <300
Select tasks whose weight is between 30 and 300 hours.

/sel -arc
Select archived tasks.

/sel -star
Select starred tasks.

/sel -trunk
Select trunk, namely, tasks with no successor.

/sel -buds
Select buds, namely, tasks with no predecessor.

/sel -t word -s 2020/1/1< -d <23:59:59 -w 30< <300 -arc -star
Specify multiple conditions.

THANK YOU FOR READING!
